│ Looking at the test failure, I can see that my initial fix was too          │
│ aggressive. The issue is that we're always freezing LHS, but in some cases  │
│ this introduces unnecessary freeze operations that can change the           │
│ semantics.                                                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ Let me analyze the problem more carefully:                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ 1. In the original code, we have a chain of selects: `%s1 = select %1, %c1, │
│ false`, then `%s2 = select %s1, %c3, false`, then `%s3 = select %s2, %c3,   │
│ false`                                                                      │
